# NotionBridge — Cursor Agent Rules
# v1.4.0 build 5 | Swift 6.3 | macOS 26+ | Apple Silicon

## Project Overview
NotionBridge is a native macOS menu bar app that runs an MCP server.
- 65 module tools across 13 modules
- Transports: stdio + SSE (legacy + Streamable HTTP)
- SecurityGate with append-only audit log
- Bundle ID: kup.solutions.notion-bridge
- Signing ID: Developer ID Application: <DEVELOPER_NAME> (<APPLE_TEAM_ID>)

## Build System
- Swift Package Manager (Package.swift at repo root)
- `Makefile` orchestrates the full pipeline
- Key targets: `make release` = clean → test → sign → notarize → dmg → verify
- Individual: `make build`, `make test`, `make sign`, `make notarize`, `make dmg`

## Source Layout
- `NotionBridge/` — main source (Config/, Modules/, Core/, Security/, Transport/)
- `NotionBridgeTests/` — unit + integration tests (308 total)
- `Info.plist` — bundle metadata (version must match Version.swift)
- `AGENTS.md` — comprehensive project documentation for AI agents

## MCP Integration
- `.cursor/mcp.json` connects to `http://localhost:9700/mcp`
- NotionBridge must be running for MCP tools to work

## Release Checklist (v1.4.0)
1. ✅ All tests pass (308/308)
2. ✅ Version bumped (1.4.0 build 5)
3. ✅ Tagged v1.4.0 and pushed to origin/main
4. ⬜ Store notarytool credentials: `xcrun notarytool store-credentials "notarytool-profile" --apple-id <APPLE_ID> --team-id <APPLE_TEAM_ID> --password <APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD>`
5. ⬜ Install create-dmg: `brew install create-dmg` (ensure brew is on PATH)
6. ⬜ Run `make release` (or step-by-step: `make sign && make notarize && make dmg && make verify`)

## Important Notes
- NotionBridge cannot build/sign/notarize itself while running
- The Makefile rpath uses `@loader_path` (not `@executable_path`)
- Sparkle framework tools are in `.build/artifacts/sparkle/Sparkle/bin/`
- Entitlements: JIT, unsigned memory, disable lib validation, apple events
